<p>That is incorrect.  In general, digital outputs on the RoboRIO still work when the robot is disabled; only PWMs and relay outputs are disabled when disabled.  The exception is on the MXP port’s shared <span class="abbreviation">PWM<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Pulse Width Modulation"></template></span>/digital pins—in that case the pin is disabled because it <em>could</em> be a <span class="abbreviation">PWM<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Pulse Width Modulation"></template></span> output.</p>
