<p><strong>Here’s a possible hacky solution. I would NOT use this with any dangerous actuators/mechanisms attached. Who knows if pin number mappings match, if this could slow down your code, or if other weird race conditions could cause unexpected behavior at any time on other pins.</strong></p>
<p>First you might test this with SSH, then automate it into your code with some C++ library. Use these commands replacing X with the Raspberry Pi’s pin number.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>raspi-gpio set X op</code> to set the pin as an output (once at the beginning of your program)</li>
<li><code>raspi-gpio set X dh</code> to set the pin high</li>
<li><code>raspi-gpio set X dl</code> to set the pin low</li>
</ul>
